            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>668</offset>
                <text>He was reevaluated at 3 years and 5 months of age.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>719</offset>
                <text>His height and annual growth rate were 75.7 cm (−5.85 SDS) and 4.1 cm/year (−2.2 SDS), respectively.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>820</offset>
                <text>He was noted to have pectus carinatum, narrow thorax and hyperlordosis in addition to his previous dysmorphological findings (Figure 1).</text>
                <annotation id="14">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000768</infon>
                    <location length="16" offset="21"/>
                    <text>pectus carinatum</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="15">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000774</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="39"/>
                    <text>narrow thorax</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="16">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0003307</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="57"/>
                    <text>hyperlordosis</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>957</offset>
                <text>Testicles, bilaterally, were found to be in scrotal sac and of a prepubertal size.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1040</offset>
                <text>A skeletal bone survey showed delayed bone age, thoracic scoliosis, slender long tubular bones, and mild metaphyseal widening (Figure 2).</text>
                <annotation id="17">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0002750</infon>
                    <location length="16" offset="30"/>
                    <text>delayed bone age</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="18">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0002943</infon>
                    <location length="18" offset="48"/>
                    <text>thoracic scoliosis</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="19">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0003100</infon>
                    <location length="26" offset="68"/>
                    <text>slender long tubular bones</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="20">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0003016</infon>
                    <location length="20" offset="105"/>
                    <text>metaphyseal widening</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1179</offset>
                <text>Serum basal growth hormone (GH), insulin-like growth factor-1 (IGF1), and IGF binding protein-3 (IGFBP3) levels were 10.2 ng/mL, 52.6 ng/mL (−1.27 SDS), and 2,921 μg/mL (2.78 SDS), respectively (Table 1).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1384</offset>
                <text>Due to normal serum basal GH levels (&gt;7 ng/ml) and peak GH responses in GH stimulation test, an IGF1 generation test (50 μg/kg/day/5 days) was performed.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1538</offset>
                <text>Following stimulation, a sufficient increase in IGF1 level was detected.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1612</offset>
                <text>Although basal GH level was found to be normal, recombinant human GH (rhGH) therapy was given because he was born small for gestational age (SGA), had severe short stature and was failed to achieve catch-up growth.</text>
                <annotation id="21">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0001518</infon>
                    <location length="25" offset="114"/>
                    <text>small for gestational age</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="22">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0004322</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="158"/>
                    <text>short stature</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1827</offset>
                <text>Although a high dose (35–50 μg/kg/day) of rhGH therapy was initiated, treatment was discontinued following 4 years due to low growth velocity (3.5–4.5 cm/year).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1989</offset>
                <text>He was 12 years old at last examination and his weight was 17.05 kg (−4.74 SDS) and height 109 cm (−5.73 SDS).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>2100</offset>
                <text>His intelligence and neuromotor development were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>2157</offset>
                <text>He was wearing a corset for his scoliosis.</text>
                <annotation id="23">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0002650</infon>
                    <location length="9" offset="32"/>
                    <text>scoliosis</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
